commit.message:
Replace uses of exec_program with execute_process

As of CMake 3.28, uses of exec_program produce a deprecation warning
suggesting to replace it with execute_process.

See https://cmake.org/cmake/help/latest/policy/CMP0153.html
Fix copy&paste error in comment

cmake: Require minimum CMake version of 3.5

More recent versions of CMake warn that support for versions
<3.5 might be dropped.

cmake: Do not set CMake policies that are already set to new

With CMake 3.0, CMP0028 and CMP0048 are set to NEW by default

Do not compile for XOP+FMA4 if compiler cannot do it

Fixes the warning below when building with the Intel compiler:

CMake Warning at cmake/VcMacros.cmake:503 (message):
  The following unknown targets where listed in the ONLY list of
  vc_compile_for_all_implementations: 'SSE+XOP+FMA4;AVX+XOP+FMA4;AVX+XOP+FMA'
Call Stack (most recent call first):
  CMakeLists.txt:121 (vc_compile_for_all_implementations)

Remove special case of MayAlias<T> for Intel C++ compiler

Also, disable warnings about attributes, same as for GCC.

Do not warn users about "broken" FMA4 and/or XOP

Even AMD processors use FMA3 these days, so on most CPUs
FMA4 is "broken". CPUs supporting XOP and FMA4 are mostly
obsolete.
